    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-31T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/97: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SERJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1">Sent by the Ambassador, Moscow, in the
                        numerical series of the Embassy’s telegrams to the Department of
                        State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-31T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 31, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1798. For the Acting Secretary from the Secretary.</p>
                <p>At the request of the Ambassador and because of the increase in work here as a
                    result (<gloss target="#t_DelAm1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">DelAm</hi>
                    </gloss> 47<note n="2" xml:id="d83fn2">Numeration of messages sent to the
                        Department of State by the American Delegation to the Moscow
                        Conference.</note>) of the Conference, I have decided to leave <persName
                        corresp="#p_BCE2">Bohlen</persName> here until the end of year. This would
                    also make him available for the contemplated meeting. I therefore request that
                    the necessary instructions be issued to him for assignment on a temporary basis
                    for two months.<note n="3" xml:id="d83fn3">On November 3, 1943, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BCE2">Bohlen</persName> was designated First Secretary of
                        the Embassy at Moscow, for temporary duty, effective upon the termination of
                        the Moscow Conference.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
